{
  "texts": [
    "7 For each 4-shot prompt, we predict the greedy answer using T = 0 and 16 sampled answers using T = 0.5.",
    "P Correct (q, a; M, T = 0) is estimated by the fraction of correct greedy answers, and P Correct (q, a; M, T > 0) by the fraction of correct sampled answers.",
    "Full details are in §C.",
    "Deriving knowledge categories from P Correct.",
    "We define the Unknown category (bottom row in Figures 2a and 2b) to represent (q, a) pairs for which M never predicts the correct answer to q."
  ]
}